                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-235-victim1767 t18320517-235-viclabel1358"></join>. I was in <placeName id="t18320517-235-crimeloc1359">High-street, St. Giles'</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320517-235-crimeloc1359" type="placeName" value="High-street, St. Giles'"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320517-235-crimeloc1359" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-235-off1356 t18320517-235-crimeloc1359"></join>, on the 13th of May - I felt a motion at my side; I turned, and saw the prisoner placing my handkerchief in his breast pocket - he ran; I pursued him, and he threw the handkerchief behind him; I still pursued- the officer saw it - he came behind me, and one of them tripped me up.</p>
               <p>PHILIP RILEY. I am an officer. I saw the prosecutor pursuing the prisoner: I saw him throw the handkerchief down and took him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Another boy took the handkerchief, and threw it on me - I threw it down, and the gentleman took me.</p>
               <p>The prisoner received a good character, and a witness promised to take him as an apprentice.</p>
